Fix: tempest plugin from git only when not in rpm

Change 1cfb5e71e64825c007b0ec184e326c7fd6c6efa5 / Ie462875a8fc1f065460111e15098ba396ac35546
did broke rpm tempest runs with some (e.g. data_processing suite) tests
enabled, when they are expected to come from rpm (they do have package
defined).

Seems just the variable name in condition is wrong.

// Though doing system wide pip install of plugin in tempest-rpm case,
// just invalidates the product under test (taints the system),
// that should be in virtualenv, but not part of this issue.

Change-Id: I8b8c9395ec7b9a0514d6b2cb9977ef99874978a2

